From: Markus Fritsche <mfritsche@localhost>
Date: Tue, 24 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ucm2: Rockchip/rk3588-es8316: add Speaker device and SectionVerb

The upstream rk3588-es8316 HiFi.conf only defines Headphones and Headset
devices.  Boards like the CoolPi CM5 GenBook route the ES8316 HPOL/HPOR
outputs through an external speaker amplifier controlled by pa-gpios in
the audio-graph-card DTS node.  Without a Speaker UCM device the HiFi
profile's only playback port is Headphones (jack-controlled), and
PipeWire falls back to the pro-audio profile with no speaker sink.

Add:

1. SectionVerb with EnableSequence that sets the Left/Right Headphone
   Mixer DAC Switch controls to "on".  These DAPM mixer switches gate
   the DAC-to-headphone-mixer path in the ES8316 and must be enabled
   for any playback.  The BootSequence in rk3588-es8316.conf already
   sets them, but DAPM's initial power evaluation after card
   registration can clear DAPM mixer control state before a stream
   opens.  Repeating the cset in the verb EnableSequence ensures the
   switches survive verb activation.

2. SectionDevice."Speaker" with:
   - PlaybackPriority 100 (lower than Headphones at 200)
   - JackHWMute "Headphones" so PipeWire mutes the speaker when
     headphones are inserted
   - Playback Polarity toggled to Normal/R Invert in Enable/Disable
     sequences (matches the existing Headphones device pattern)

Tested on CoolPi CM5 GenBook (RK3588, ES8316 codec on I2C7,
audio-graph-card with pa-gpios on GPIO1_PA6).

Generated-by: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Signed-off-by: Markus Fritsche <mfritsche@localhost>
---
 ucm2/Rockchip/rk3588-es8316/HiFi.conf | 27 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 27 insertions(+)

--- a/ucm2/Rockchip/rk3588-es8316/HiFi.conf
+++ b/ucm2/Rockchip/rk3588-es8316/HiFi.conf
@@ -1,3 +1,30 @@
+SectionVerb {
+	EnableSequence [
+		cset "name='Left Headphone Mixer Left DAC Switch' on"
+		cset "name='Right Headphone Mixer Right DAC Switch' on"
+	]
+}
+
+SectionDevice."Speaker" {
+	Comment "Built-in Speakers"
+
+	EnableSequence [
+		cset "name='Playback Polarity' 'Normal'"
+	]
+
+	DisableSequence [
+		cset "name='Playback Polarity' 'R Invert'"
+	]
+
+	Value {
+		PlaybackPriority 100
+		PlaybackPCM "hw:${CardId}"
+		PlaybackMixerElem "Headphone Mixer"
+		PlaybackMasterElem "DAC"
+		JackHWMute "Headphones"
+	}
+}
+
 SectionDevice."Headphones" {
 	Comment "Headphones"

